Meet the kung fu master 👀

Mantids are born with excellent eyesight. However, their keen eyes are no equal match for that of a hungry jumping spider. But they do have one trick up their sleeve when it comes to self-defence: partaking in a bit of kung-fu. This self-defence mechanism serves to confuse its predator, making the insect appear bigger than it actually is. But, the fight to stay alive doesn’t end there…

Will safety in numbers help them catch their prey?

node.text:
Me when they say to act natural 👀⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Lions (Panthera leo) have famously acquired the title of ‘King of the Jungle’. However, the title is a little misleading as lions don’t actually live in jungles. Their habits include scrubland, grasslands, savannahs and rocky hills, but not jungles! ⁣⁣⁣
In Serengeti II, we return to an unspoilt corner of Africa’s Serengeti for more real life animal drama. There’s humour, heartbreak and nail biting tension. Find out more via the link in our bio.⁣⁣⁣

Female giraffes give birth standing up, meaning newborns are literally dropped into the world! 🦒⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
